==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Champertor
<hw>Cham"per*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>champarteur</ets> a divider of fields or field rent. See
<er>Champerty</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One guilty of
champerty; one who purchases a suit, or the right of suing, and carries
it on at his own expense, in order to obtain a share of the
gain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Champerty</ent>⟦br⟧
